commit.message:
Replace install command with $(INSTALL) variable

Some Linux distributions prefer to use "INSTALL='install -p'" during 'make
install' to preserve the original file timestamps when packaging signify.

Original author: Robert-André Mauchin
Release version 31

commit.message:
Vendor the few files actually needed from libbsd

Instead of downloading and building a full copy of libbsd, include in
the tree the few files needed by Signify picked from version 0.11.3
(current stable) and arrange to build them directly from the single
Makefile. To make things easier, use libbsd overlayed.

As a bonus, include conftests for optional system functions that
progname.c can make use of.

As a side effect of using libbsd overlayed, this patch also reverts
some of the local changes applied to the files imported from the
OpenBSD CVS.
